				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is one thing that I have been bothered with for a while, and I just sent /feedback in game, and wanted to post here.
<br />
Level 65 mages get a spell called, Call of the Arch Mage, which allows them to charm elemental mobs. Those of you who have been to BOT and seen a mage or chanter charm a mob, will understand how nice this spell is for them.
<br />
This leaves beastlords as the only pet class that is not able to charm.
<br />
I think we should get a level 65 spell, called Call of the Savage Lord, that is the same as the mage spell, but specific to animals rather than elementals. I dont know if this has been brought up as an issue before, and im too lazy to search for the topic.  I think this is simply a balance issue. We should not be the only pet class without the ability to charm.  Animals cannot be found in every zone, and we should have the same level restrictions as mages, so I dont think this will overpower the beastlord in any way. If anyone wants to discuss this, please feel free to make a character on MT and send me a tell. I dont visit the message boards too often, and I would rather have a live conversation. I would welcome any conversation, especially from the level 65 beastlords.
<br />

<br />
Wildkard
<br />
65 Beastlord
<br />
Morrell-Thule</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Wildkard on Fri Feb 28, 2003 11:18 am; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
