<br />
    Ummm, according to the lore behind the class, we do not summon our warders, and they are not spirits.   The whole thing about our warders being spirits came about because the PR guy at VI/SoE needed to come up with a reason our warders were on a 5 our time limit before.   According to the lore, we form a life bond with a seingle creature.  This single creature gains more intelligence and a stronger affinity for communication with their bond partner, us.  Further when we use the Spirit Of spells, we are imbuing them with the spirits of.  We do not summon, we do not charm, we merely ask the blessings of the spirits around us.
<br />

<br />
   Again, according to the lore behind the class, Mages <span style="font-weight: bold">force</span> an elemental creature to do their bidding.   The very first command a Mage gives to the elemental creature is to come to them, hence the summoning mechanism in EQ.   Thus by extension, it would make sense for a Mage to be able to force an elemental in it's home plane to do their bidding.   Now, since EQ does not have the old D&D style command and dominate spells, VI/SoE has to rely on the charm mechanism.<br />_________________<br /><ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Elder Kaatt</a>, Sixty-Five Year Old Khati Sha Feral Lord of Xev.<ul><li>BST65.281/Xv h++ 4(3.8)khp 4.1km ft5 r10 !G&gt;++++ e++ o T++ L++ H- f+ g b !t D+ X@</ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</a>, Coercion Technician of the Sixty-Fifth Tier of Xev.<ul><li>ENC65.19/Xv h-- 1.6(1.9)khp 3.7km ft1 r3 !G&gt;++++ e+&gt;++++ o T++ L-- H- f+ g b(@) c+&gt;++++ t-&gt;! D+ X@</ul></ul></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
