				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, so to satisfy all the lore problems. Let's say that beastlords learn how to bond with an animal so effectively, that we are able to bond with other animals for a certain amout of time, but not permanently. This would not violate any of the lore, it would just be an advancement of our ability to the highest level, which in EQ is level 65.  We become so attuned to our animal, that we can use this to communicate with other animals and ask for their help.  Thus, balancing the pet classes, which is what this post is about anyway. The spell would be limited anyway, because there arent a lot of animals that could be charmed in the planes.
<br />
 And remember, we are talking about level 65 here, the penultimate beastlord. This is a high end balance issue, not one that will be seen anywhere except at level 65.
<br />

<br />
Wildkard</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
