			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm would not "balance" us with other pet classes. We are already pretty well balanced with the other pet classes.  Our pets are comparable, our pet buffs are comparable, and what we lack in nuking we make up in melee ability. If you want a descrition of pet classes it would go something like:
<br />

<br />
Mages : Best pet, best DD at the cost of lack of escape, durability, and lack of "utility" outside of summon spells.  Charm buys them LIMITED opportunities.
<br />

<br />
Necros : 2nd best pets. Best DOTS. Has escape ability, lacks durabilty and has some utility for groups. Charm buys them LIMITED opportunities.
<br />

<br />
Beastlord : 3rd best pets. Best range of pet buffs. Escape ability, durability, and good utility. Charm would buy us LIMITED opportunities.
<br />

<br />
Enchanter : 4th best pet. Uncontrollable pets until AA's. Escape ability, lacks durabilty outside of spells, incredible utility. Charm is part of their UTILITY.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The other 5 "pet" classes(Shaman, druid, SK, Wizard and cleric) merely have pets as an extension of damage.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Charm would buy us no increase in balance with other casters. We are pretty well balanced in that department. The ONLY thing I could see giving us would be allow us to cast our pet imbues on other pets. THats all.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
