				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm Elemental is used by mages to try to solo in pop. It is the only way a Mage can solo in PoP , and it is unreliable at best because Mages ( like BL ) cannot snare the mob. 
<br />

<br />
For some perspective - one of the attractions of the BL for me is to be able to solo in PoP - and is one of the reasons why I have hung up my Mage (except when the Guild needs a high level Mage on a raid ).  I do not see anything wrong with BL getting it, except that druids might cry that they have to share the charm animal thing, but from a balance stand point, it will make 0 difference in the end. You will still end up using your 64 warder after a few CR's , because unlike the Mage CotAM, the Beastie has better options already available to him .</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
